  "body": [
    "Bhai Gurfateh Singh Shant was born to Mata Kulwinder Kaur and Sardar Kulwant Singh Shant on 23rd September 1986 in the locality of Khurla Kingra, Jalandhar. He is the youngest of 5 siblings which include Amritpal Kaur, Gursharan Kaur, Iqbal Singh and Daler Singh. He received his initial training from his grandfather and father. Then he started his training with his paternal uncle, Bhai Gurmeet Singh Shant who has greatly influenced his art. Subsequently, he went on to complete his B.A. in Sangeet from Pracheen Kala Kendra in Chandigarh and a course in Gurmat from the Sikh Missionary College in Ludhiana. Currently, he is employed as a Hazoori Raagi with the Delhi Sikh Gurdwara Committee and he also teaches music in Sri Guru Gobind Singh College of Commerce in Pritam Pura, New Delhi. Besides that, he is also involved with other ‘Sewas’ including judging the program ‘Kaun De Heere’ and conducting interviews of jathas wishing to apply for the position of Hazoori Raagis. He is adept in Gurmat Sangeet, Taranas, Guldastas, Thumris and is also extremely well versed with the Baani of Guru Gobind Singh Ji. Aside from singing, he also plays the tabla and writes very well. He formed a ‘jatha’ at the age of 15 and has performed in various Kirtan Darbars since then. He has also traveled extensively around the world including countries such as Malaysia, Thailand, UAE and more. If anyone has more recordings of Bhai Gurfateh Singh Shant to share, please contact us."
